Arco Unit Signs Agreement
   For Sale of Natural Gas
The Chinese government holds a 51% interest in the
project, while Arco China Inc., operator of the Yacheng 13-1
gas field, holds a 34.3% interest. Arco China's joint venture
partner, Kufpec (China) Inc., a unit of Kuwait Foreign
Petroleum Exploration Co., holds a 14.7% interest.
   The Yacheng field, discovered in 1983, has recoverable gas
reserves estimated at 3 trillion cubic feet. Production is
expected to begin in January 1996 and reach a peak of 330
million cubic feet a day.